00:12:48.040 --> 00:12:49.570
So when they're
checking your card,

00:12:49.570 --> 00:12:52.450
it's just a credit card
company checking its records

00:12:52.450 --> 00:12:54.790
to see if they're
willing to issue

00:12:54.790 --> 00:12:56.320
the receivable to Starbucks.

00:12:56.320 --> 00:12:58.028
GARY GENSLER: So what
you're really doing

00:12:58.028 --> 00:13:01.480
is you're spending a form of
money called bank deposits.

00:13:01.480 --> 00:13:04.000
And your bank deposit
is going to go down,

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:06.423
and what's Starbucks
bank deposit going to do?

00:13:06.423 --> 00:13:07.090
AUDIENCE: Go up.

00:13:07.090 --> 00:13:08.600
GARY GENSLER: Go up.

00:13:08.600 --> 00:13:11.830
So three forms of money--

00:13:11.830 --> 00:13:16.080
the cash, the deposits,
and the reserves,

00:13:16.080 --> 00:13:18.840
because the central bank
is giving some money.

00:13:21.410 --> 00:13:25.430
All of this is handled in
accounts in a ledger structure.

00:13:25.430 --> 00:13:26.960
And we talked about it.

00:13:26.960 --> 00:13:29.540
So the accounts-- there's
central bank accounts,

00:13:29.540 --> 00:13:30.710
and there are bank accounts.

00:13:30.710 --> 00:13:35.060
It's just accounts are ledgers,
I've just changed the words.

00:13:35.060 --> 00:13:37.910
And it's moved through a
system, a payment system

00:13:37.910 --> 00:13:40.130
that we talked about last
week-- and I'm putting to.

00:13:40.130 --> 00:13:43.550
Real-time gross settlement
is that little box up there.

00:13:43.550 --> 00:13:47.300
Real-time gross settlement
is a system between banks

00:13:47.300 --> 00:13:48.560
and a central bank.

00:13:48.560 --> 00:13:50.510
Almost every country
has some form

00:13:50.510 --> 00:13:52.520
of real-time gross
settlement system.

00:13:52.520 --> 00:13:58.830
Here in the US, we might
call it the Fed wire, or ACH.

00:13:58.830 --> 00:14:02.998
I see Ali-- is ACH real-time
gross settlement, or maybe not?

00:14:02.998 --> 00:14:04.290
AUDIENCE: No, they're not real.

00:14:04.290 --> 00:14:05.350
GARY GENSLER: Just the Fed wire.

00:14:05.350 --> 00:14:06.850
AUDIENCE: There's
another one, but I

00:14:06.850 --> 00:14:08.400
