00:14:08.400 --> 00:14:09.283
GARY GENSLER: Chips?

00:14:09.283 --> 00:14:09.950
AUDIENCE: Chips.

00:14:09.950 --> 00:14:12.033
GARY GENSLER: Chips-- so
in the US, we have chips,

00:14:12.033 --> 00:14:14.400
and the Fed wire are both
real-time gross settlement.

00:14:17.550 --> 00:14:22.480
That's between banks
and the central bank.

00:14:22.480 --> 00:14:24.620
And then you have all
sorts of systems--

00:14:24.620 --> 00:14:27.940
what's in that little box
is not as important to read,

00:14:27.940 --> 00:14:30.580
is basically to
move between banks.

00:14:30.580 --> 00:14:34.420
So that's central banking
and how it fits into money.

