00:20:20.760 --> 00:20:24.390
on the central bank's ledger.

00:20:24.390 --> 00:20:31.120
Because the central bank
could, if they wish to,

00:20:31.120 --> 00:20:32.380
deny use of this.

00:20:32.380 --> 00:20:34.300
They haven't, they
haven't for decades,

00:20:34.300 --> 00:20:36.430
but I'm saying
somebody could say,

00:20:36.430 --> 00:20:39.190
that's a bad serial number.

00:20:39.190 --> 00:20:41.950
But most people would say
that $20 piece of linen

00:20:41.950 --> 00:20:45.155
is a store of value.

00:20:45.155 --> 00:20:46.780
AUDIENCE: I was going
to ask, would you

00:20:46.780 --> 00:20:51.280
expect the velocity of these
